                <h2>Guiding Vision Transformers Towards Justification</h2>
                <p class="project-subtitle"><em>An Overview of Feature Alignment and Justifiability in ViTs</em></p>
                
                <div class="project-block">
                    <h3>Abstract & Overview</h3>
                    <p>
                        Standard Vision Transformers (ViTs) extract visual features effectively, but their decision-making process often lacks interpretability. This research introduces a framework designed to guide Vision Transformers toward features that align with human visual perspectives and ground-truth justification maps.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="project-block">
                    <h3>Methodology & Demo Highlights</h3>
                    <p>
                        Below is a conceptual walkthrough of how feature extraction alignment is enforced during training:
                    </p>
                    
                    <ul class="academic-list">
                        <li><strong>Feature Map Extraction:</strong> Extracting output embeddings from final transformer layers.</li>
                        <li><strong>Justification Loss Alignment:</strong> Penalizing spatial attention maps that stray from target regions.</li>
                        <li><strong>Evaluation:</strong> Testing alignment against custom metrics for grounding and fidelity.</li>
                    </ul>
